text: Émile Grumiaux was an archer from France. He was born on 11 June 1861 and died on 18 May 1932. Grumiaux competed at the 1900 Summer Olympics.Émile GrumiauxEmile GRUMIAUX == References == Category:1861 births Category:1932 deaths Category:French archers Category:Olympic gold medalists for France Category:People from Pas-de-Calais Category:Sportspeople from Hauts-de-France
